# Authentication

The API uses **API Key authentication with Bearer tokens**.

All requests must include the API key in the **Authorization header**.

---

## How to Obtain Credentials

1. Create a developer account.
2. Navigate to **Developer Dashboard → API Keys**
3. Generate your **Secret API Key**

Example:
sk_live_91dhdh82hdk2hd82h

Keep this key secure. Never expose it in frontend code.

---

## Required Headers

| Header | Description |
|------|------|
| Authorization | Bearer API Key |
| Content-Type | application/json |

Example:
Authorization: Bearer sk_live_91dhdh82hdk2hd82h
Content-Type: application/json

---

## Example Authenticated Request

```bash
curl https://api.payflowcloud.com/v1/payments \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk_live_91dhdh82hdk2hd82h" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"

---


# Endpoints

Create Payment

## HTTP Method
POST
---

## URL
/payments

---

## Description
Creates a new payment transaction.

---

## Request Parameters

| Parameter      | Type    | Required | Description                              |
| -------------- | ------- | -------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| amount         | integer | Yes      | Payment amount in smallest currency unit |
| currency       | string  | Yes      | Currency code (USD, EUR, NGN)            |
| customer_id    | string  | Yes      | Unique customer identifier               |
| payment_method | string  | Yes      | Card, bank_transfer, wallet              |
| description    | string  | No       | Transaction description                  |

---

## JSON Request Example

{ 
  "amount": 5000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "customer_id": "cus_847382",
  "payment_method": "card",
  "description": "Premium subscription"
}

---

## JSON Response Example

{
  "id": "pay_9384723",
  "status": "succeeded",
  "amount": 5000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "customer_id": "cus_847382",
  "created_at": "2026-03-11T10:20:45Z"
}

---

## Error Responses

| Status Code | Meaning               |
| ----------- | --------------------- |
| 400         | Invalid request       |
| 401         | Unauthorized          |
| 402         | Payment failed        |
| 500         | Internal server error |


Example Error:

{
  "error": {
    "type": "invalid_request",
    "message": "Amount must be greater than zero"
  }
}

---

## Edge Cases

- Payment declined by issuing bank

- Invalid currency code

- Duplicate transaction request

- Insufficient customer balance

