## Retrieve Payment

### HTTP Method
GET

---

### URL
/payments/{payment_id}

---

### Description

Retrieves details of a specific payment transaction.

| Parameter  | Type   | Description       |
| ---------- | ------ | ----------------- |
| payment_id | string | Unique payment ID |

---

Example Request

GET /payments/pay_9384723

---

### JSON Response

{
  "id": "pay_9384723",
  "status": "succeeded",
  "amount": 5000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "customer_id": "cus_847382",
  "created_at": "2026-03-11T10:20:45Z"
}

---

## Refund Payment

### HTTP Method
POST

---

### URL
/payments/{payment_id}/refund

---

### Description

Refunds a previously completed payment.

---

### Request Body

| Parameter | Type    | Required | Description   |
| --------- | ------- | -------- | ------------- |
| amount    | integer | No       | Refund amount |

---

Example Request

{
  "amount": 5000
}

---

Response Example

{
  "refund_id": "ref_827382",
  "payment_id": "pay_9384723",
  "status": "processed",
  "amount": 5000
}

---

### Error Responses

| Code | Description              |
| ---- | ------------------------ |
| 404  | Payment not found        |
| 409  | Payment already refunded |
| 402  | Refund failed            |

---

