# Rate Limiting

The API limits requests to:
100 requests per minute per API key

If exceeded, the API returns:
HTTP 429 Too Many Requests

Example:

{
  "error": "Rate limit exceeded"
}

---

# Pagination

Endpoints that return lists support cursor-based pagination.

## Parameters:

| Parameter      | Description               |
| -------------- | ------------------------- |
| limit          | Number of items to return |
| starting_after | Cursor for next page      |

Example:
GET /payments?limit=20&starting_after=pay_123

---

# Webhooks

Webhooks notify your application when payment events occur.

Example Events

| Event             | Description       |
| ----------------- | ----------------- |
| payment.succeeded | Payment completed |
| payment.failed    | Payment declined  |
| refund.processed  | Refund successful |

Webhook Payload Example

{
  "event": "payment.succeeded",
  "data": {
    "payment_id": "pay_9384723",
    "amount": 5000,
    "currency": "USD"
  }
}

---

# Best Practices
- Secure Your API Keys

- Never expose secret keys in client-side code.

- Implement Idempotency

- Use idempotency keys to prevent duplicate transactions.

- Handle Failures Gracefully

- Always handle payment failures and retry logic.

- Verify Webhook Signatures

- Ensure webhook requests originate from the payment provider.

---

# Common Errors & Troubleshooting

| Error               | Cause                     | Solution                               |
| ------------------- | ------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Unauthorized        | Invalid API key           | Verify Authorization header            |
| Invalid request     | Incorrect parameters      | Check request body                     |
| Payment failed      | Bank declined transaction | Prompt user for another payment method |
| Rate limit exceeded | Too many requests         | Implement retry with backoff           |

